alerts.title: Flash Flood Watch for Snohomish, WA
alerts.description:
...FLASH FLOOD WATCH NOW IN EFFECT THROUGH MONDAY AFTERNOON...
THE FLASH FLOOD WATCH IS NOW IN EFFECT FOR
* A PORTION OF WESTERN WASHINGTON...INCLUDING THE FOLLOWING
COUNTY... SNOHOMISH.
* THROUGH MONDAY AFTERNOON
* A LANDSLIDE BLOCKED THE NORTH FORK OF THE STILLAGUAMISH RIVER
NEAR OSO. WHEN AND IF THE LANDSLIDE-INDUCED BLOCKAGE RELEASES...
FLASH FLOODING DOWNSTREAM TO ARLINGTON IS POSSIBLE.
* THE MOST LIKELY RELEASE OF WATER IS THAT IT PIPES THROUGH AND
AROUND THE DEBRIS AND...PARTICULARLY IF COMBINED WITH
OVER-TOPPING THE BLOCKAGE...THE WATER CUTS DOWN A CHANNEL
THROUGH THE DEBRIS. THIS COULD STILL RESULT IN A RAPID RISE OF
WATER AND IS A DANGEROUS SITUATION.
* THE GREATEST THREAT OF FLOODING FROM A RELEASE OF THE IMPOUNDED
WATER IS IN THE VICINITY OF THE SLIDE DEBRIS BLOCKAGE...
IMMEDIATELY DOWNSTREAM OF IT...AND IN THE STREAM CHANNEL DOWN TO
THE CONFLUENCE WITH THE SOUTH FORK. PRELIMINARY DAM BREAK MODEL
SCENARIOS SHOW THE RESULTING FLOWS WOULD HAVE THE NORTH FORK AT
ARLINGTON GAGE CRESTING BELOW FLOOD STAGE BUT COULD RESULT IN
SOME MINOR FLOODING.
* ROADS...SOME HOUSES...AND MANY FIELDS COULD FLOOD IF A FLASH
FLOOD OCCURS. ESCAPE MAY BE DIFFICULT FROM RAPIDLY RISING
WATERS.

alerts.title: Flood Warning for Snohomish, WA
alerts.description:
CORRECTED FOR FORECAST TEXT.
...THE FLOOD WARNING CONTINUES FOR THE FOLLOWING RIVERS IN
WASHINGTON...
NORTH FORK STILLAGUAMISH RIVER NEAR ARLINGTON AFFECTING SNOHOMISH
COUNTY.
.FLOOD BULLETIN NO. 4
CENTRAL WEST REGION
A LANDSLIDE BLOCKED THE NORTH FORK OF THE STILLAGUAMISH RIVER
SATURDAY MORNING. WATER IS BACKING UP BEHIND THE LANDSLIDE. SOME
FLOODING IS OCCURRING UPSTREAM OF THE SLIDE...EAST OF OSO AS THE
WATER FLOWING DOWN THE RIVER INTO THE SLIDE AREA POOLS UP BEHIND THE
BLOCKAGE. THIS FLOODING COULD IMPACT AREA ROADS AND SR530.
...FLOOD WARNING EXTENDED UNTIL MONDAY AFTERNOON...
THE FLOOD WARNING CONTINUES FOR
THE NORTH FORK STILLAGUAMISH RIVER NEAR ARLINGTON
* UNTIL MONDAY AFTERNOON.
* AT 11:15 AM SUNDAY THE STAGE WAS 2.9 FEET.
* FLOOD STAGE IS 13.0 FEET.
* THE POOL OF WATER UPSTREAM OF THE OSO AREA LANDSLIDE ACROSS THE
NORTH FORK STILLAGUAMISH RIVER WILL CONTINUE TO DEEPEN AND SPREAD AS
THE RIVER CONTINUES TO FLOW INTO THE BLOCKAGE. THIS WILL CONTINUE TO
GET WORSE UNTIL THE WATER STARTS TO MAKE A WAY THROUGH THE BLOCKAGE
AND CAN BEGIN TO DRAIN.
&&
